1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,235
T/N: I think this date does a good job with world-building. I just want to add something mentioned in the PV song lyrics and other guys’ dates. There's this thing called Iris Device, which is a lens implanted in everyone’s eye at the age of seven.

2
00:00:02,235 --> 00:00:03,837
It's directly linked to a multidimensional scoring system that monitors what you see and tracks your vitals as part of deciding your score. I guess it’s similar to those sci-fi contact lenses? Anyway, yea that’s all for now-

3
00:00:03,837 --> 00:00:07,908
The sound of the prison gates slowly closing rings out from afar, shattering the silence of the space.

4
00:00:07,908 --> 00:00:12,480
Almost simultaneously, my lens also flickers slightly.

5
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:18,020
I slow my steps, raise a hand, and tap the corner of my frame. In the next second, a fluorescent admin interface spreads out across the lens's view.

6
00:00:18,020 --> 00:00:22,158
A very small prompt box appears at the top of the layered notification bar: "Execution in two hours."

7
00:00:22,158 --> 00:00:25,395
I glance at the time and pick up my pace a little.

8
00:00:25,395 --> 00:00:31,068
All criminals held in this prison must undergo bi-monthly systematic scoring to quantify the degree of ‘repentance’.

9
00:00:31,068 --> 00:00:36,808
If their scores show no increase for three consecutive times, they are deemed ‘incorrigible’.

10
00:00:36,808 --> 00:00:43,315
The prison will then administer punishment by erasing the criminal's key memories and reshaping a sound personality through visual education.

11
00:00:43,315 --> 00:00:47,787
And as medical staff, carrying out this punishment is the core part of my work beyond daily treatments.

12
00:00:47,787 --> 00:00:54,962
It's just that recently, the criminals have been relatively well-behaved, and for months, this is the first time I’ve received an execution notice.

13
00:00:54,962 --> 00:00:58,766
I wonder what kind of heinous, unrepentant person I will deal with this time...

14
00:00:58,766 --> 00:01:02,671
Thinking about the tedious procedures ahead, I can’t help but sigh softly and helplessly close the interface before me.

15
00:01:02,671 --> 00:01:07,776
After clearing identity verification at the gate to the high-risk area, I continue down the corridor.

16
00:01:07,776 --> 00:01:12,348
The faint sound of footsteps in the distance gradually grows clearer, mingled with the muffled scrape of chains dragging across the floor.

17
00:01:12,348 --> 00:01:16,353
I lift my head absentmindedly, only for a familiar figure to suddenly come into view, catching me off guard.

18
00:01:16,353 --> 00:01:22,293
....Lucien walks from the opposite direction under the watch of two guards, his hands bound in chains, hanging loosely in front of him.

19
00:01:22,293 --> 00:01:27,232
His prison uniform seems ill-fitting, slipping off his shoulders as he moves, revealing his slender neck.

20
00:01:27,232 --> 00:01:32,504
Yet the corners of his lips hold a hint of a relaxed smile, as if he is not heading toward the depths of the prison, but rather toward a sunlit garden.

21
00:01:32,504 --> 00:01:37,710
On the contrary, the guards look tense as if facing a lethal enemy.

22
00:01:37,710 --> 00:01:45,319
Upon seeing me, a glint of surprise seems to flash through those dark eyes. Lucien takes the initiative to stop walking, coming to a halt just an arm’s length away from me.

23
00:01:45,319 --> 00:01:51,693
Lucien: At this hour, why isn't Miss Section Chief resting in the office area?

24
00:01:51,693 --> 00:01:57,466
MC: Perhaps you should know better why you didn’t cherish your opportunities.

25
00:01:57,466 --> 00:02:02,806
MC: Not only will you have your memories erased, but you’re also ‘dragging’ me into working overtime.

26
00:02:02,806 --> 00:02:06,944
Lucien helplessly spreads out his hands, the restraints on his wrists glaringly conspicuous.

27
00:02:06,944 --> 00:02:10,681
Lucien: I’m also very surprised about this.

28
00:02:10,681 --> 00:02:16,588
Lucien: Clearly, I’ve been very well-behaved recently.

29
00:02:16,588 --> 00:02:21,994
MC: The system doesn't misjudge. It seems like you're not only extremely bad, but you also lack self-awareness.

30
00:02:21,994 --> 00:02:28,668
Probably sensing the absence of sympathy in my voice, Lucien lets out a sigh that seems tinged with regret.

31
00:02:28,668 --> 00:02:36,744
The chains binding his wrists are suddenly pulled taut. I look up to see a guard beside him turning to address me.

32
00:02:36,744 --> 00:02:41,049
Guard: Section Chief MC, please refrain from communicating with Number 0525.

33
00:02:41,049 --> 00:02:46,188
Guard: Several managers who have been in contact with him have recently experienced a drop in their scores.

34
00:02:46,188 --> 00:02:50,893
MC: Thank you, but my psyche has never been influenced by criminals.

35
00:02:50,893 --> 00:02:57,501
MC: Otherwise, the warden wouldn’t have specifically assigned me to perform the execution.

36
00:02:57,501 --> 00:03:04,876
My tone carries faint arrogance. The guard pauses briefly, his expression shifting almost imperceptibly before traces of respect surface.

37
00:03:04,876 --> 00:03:09,314
Guard: ...As expected of the prison’s youngest medical section chief.

38
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:14,353
Guard: A criminal who is this dangerous still needs your direct intervention to command control.

39
00:03:14,353 --> 00:03:18,825
MC: Aren't you going to escort Number 0525 back? You've already wasted quite a bit of time.

40
00:03:18,825 --> 00:03:23,664
I ignore the gaze trailing me and speak up to remind them. The guards nod, turning to sternly urge Lucien.

41
00:03:23,664 --> 00:03:29,003
He lowers his eyes obediently and moves at a leisurely pace. I also withdraw my gaze and continue walking toward the office area.

42
00:03:29,003 --> 00:03:37,113
The metallic scrape of shackles intermingles with the click-clack staccato of high heels. In the fleeting moment we pass each other, the periphery of my vision suddenly plunges into shadow.

43
00:03:37,113 --> 00:03:44,120
Lucien suddenly leans in close, his whisper—accompanied by the warmth of his breath— brushing just near yet distant against my ear.

44
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:48,859
Lucien: I've been waiting for this day for a long time.

45
00:03:48,859 --> 00:03:55,367
Lucien: Let me see what you've learned in this place.

46
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:57,235
Guard: Number 0525!!

47
00:03:57,235 --> 00:04:03,776
The chain around Lucien’s neck jerks taut. I take half a step back and coldly spit out a word.

48
00:04:03,776 --> 00:04:10,851
MC: ...Lunatic.

49
00:04:11,051 --> 00:04:14,021
(T/N: I find it neat that while Lucien affectionately calls her 小疯子 (xiǎo fēngzi – little lunatic) in Dawn Date (The Steadfast Soldier AU), here it’s her turn to call him 疯子 😆)

50
00:04:15,690 --> 00:04:21,663
Countless streamers were projected across the azure sky, the melodious tune of the school anthem gradually fading as the flying media player departed.

51
00:04:21,663 --> 00:04:33,610
From time to time, young men and women cheered as they tossed their graduation caps into the sky, adjusting their robots to capture this beautiful scene.

52
00:04:33,610 --> 00:04:42,553
Although technology has undergone tremendous changes, the graduation ceremony at Mainland University still adheres to the old-time celebration traditions from a century ago.

53
00:04:42,553 --> 00:04:48,660
I was gazing listlessly at the scene outside the window when I heard someone behind me speaking in a gentle voice.

54
00:04:48,660 --> 00:04:53,833
Lucien: Who knows the next time when we'll meet again.

55
00:04:53,833 --> 00:05:00,107
MC: Mentor, don’t say that. Even if work keeps me busy, I’ll still come back to visit you.

56
00:05:00,107 --> 00:05:07,782
MC: If it weren't for your guidance these past few years, with my mental state, it would have been very difficult to maintain a stable high score of 85 in the system.

57
00:05:07,782 --> 00:05:17,994
Lucien: I've also cherished these years of talking with you, MC. By the way, have you already decided on where you want to go after graduation?

58
00:05:17,994 --> 00:05:22,899
A vague heaviness sank in my heart. I looked away from the window and, maintaining politeness, forced the corners of my mouth into a smile.

59
00:05:22,899 --> 00:05:27,071
MC: The system recommended four or five places tailored to my score, I’ll just pick from those.

60
00:05:27,071 --> 00:05:32,677
MC: After all, every employer needs to check the score. There’s hardly any room for freedom to choose, is there?

61
00:05:32,677 --> 00:05:37,416
A cup of hot tea was slid before me, its rising, swirling steam blurring his gaze from view.

62
00:05:37,416 --> 00:05:42,955
Lucien: But I think you don't necessarily have to heed its suggestions.

63
00:05:42,955 --> 00:05:47,961
I was taken aback, looking at this renowned instructor somewhat incredulously.

64
00:05:47,961 --> 00:05:53,934
…For as long as I can remember, the system has been the most important part of the societal evaluation framework.

65
00:05:53,934 --> 00:05:59,841
Everyone begins receiving scores starting at the age of seven. Choosing a major, a job, even a spouse… every major life decision must be made with reference to one’s score.

66
00:05:59,841 --> 00:06:05,014
Those who achieve high scores naturally enjoy greater access to societal resources, while even the freedoms low scorers possess are constrained.

67
00:06:05,014 --> 00:06:11,054
Individuals like Lucien, whose scores place them at the pinnacle of the social pyramid, can easily attain everything they desire… whether wealth or the golden ticket into the ruling class.

68
00:06:11,054 --> 00:06:16,427
Wouldn't someone with such vested interests be even more inclined to uphold the system's judgments? Then why would he say something like that?

69
00:06:16,427 --> 00:06:20,832
MC: ...Mentor, what do you mean?

70
00:06:20,832 --> 00:06:28,006
Lucien: The work one pursues should be considered from many dimensions, including interests, development, and many more.

71
00:06:28,006 --> 00:06:34,247
Lucien: Score is merely a number, not the sole decision criterion.

72
00:06:34,247 --> 00:06:39,553
My actions faltered briefly as I let out a soft "Hm?"

73
00:06:39,553 --> 00:06:44,992
MC: But can human judgment truly be more scientific than the system?

74
00:06:44,992 --> 00:06:51,300
MC: It was only after the multidimensional scoring system was born that society achieved the most efficient resource allocation mechanism.

75
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:56,906
MC: Moreover, the Mainland’s average annual economic growth rate increased by 9.8 percentage points compared to before the system's implementation, and even the crime rate...

76
00:06:56,906 --> 00:07:01,444
My fluent recitation stumbled mid-sentence as I met his smiling gaze.

77
00:07:01,444 --> 00:07:04,815
Lucien: So MC has always been this knowledgeable about the system.

78
00:07:04,815 --> 00:07:11,222
Lucien: It was a mistake on its part not to assign you to the system operation and maintenance major.

79
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:16,328
MC: …It’s almost impossible to forget this kind of information that’s been pushed at us since childhood.

80
00:07:16,328 --> 00:07:21,834
I muttered in a low voice, then belatedly pressed my lips into a tight line as I glanced at him tentatively.

81
00:07:21,834 --> 00:07:30,244
Outside the window, the melody of the school anthem became clear once more alongside the hum of flying machines. Lucien quietly looked at me, a subtle curve suddenly appearing at the corner of his lips.

82
00:07:30,244 --> 00:07:35,516
Lucien: Actually, I only need you to answer one question.

83
00:07:35,516 --> 00:07:41,723
Lucien: MC, do you truly place unwavering faith in the system's judgment?

84
00:07:43,025 --> 00:07:47,397
System: “Drug formulation has been completed.”

85
00:07:47,397 --> 00:07:52,636
An eye-catching prompt box suddenly popped up from the lower-right corner of the lens interface, flashing rhythmically.

86
00:07:52,636 --> 00:07:58,142
MC: Mentor Xu…

87
00:07:58,142 --> 00:08:03,348
I pick up the drug solution from the pharmacy bench, murmuring softly.

88
00:08:03,348 --> 00:08:09,655
The memory from the graduation ceremony is still vivid, but the person who spoke with measured grace across from me that day has now become a criminal.

89
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:15,161
After that consultation, I still chose the prison among the job placements recommended by the system.

90
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:21,001
I never expected that not long after, I’d abruptly see one breaking news story after another about Lucien.

91
00:08:21,001 --> 00:08:27,275
His photos dominate the pages of countless media outlets, and the headlines incite an even greater public outcry.

92
00:08:27,275 --> 00:08:31,513
”Renowned Psychologist Suspected of Interfering with System Standards”—this incident has stirred a massive uproar.

93
00:08:31,513 --> 00:08:37,887
The scoring time for that month was even postponed by a week to conduct an item-by-item audit and recalibration of entries he had handled.

94
00:08:37,887 --> 00:08:42,526
Everyone who had close contact with him, including me, was urgently interrogated and retested.

95
00:08:42,526 --> 00:08:47,765
Fortunately, my system score remains stable. Relying on this, I haven’t faced any further repercussions.

96
00:08:47,765 --> 00:08:50,568
What about him?

97
00:08:50,568 --> 00:08:55,941
When he gazes through the bars at that unchanging sky, does he think of his once free and bright life?

98
00:08:55,941 --> 00:09:01,414
The final instrument is now fully prepared. I lower my gaze to sweep a glance over it. Collecting my thoughts, I walk toward the execution chamber.

99
00:09:02,949 --> 00:09:06,486
The surveillance camera’s red dot flickers faintly, rotating in time with my unhurried footsteps.

100
00:09:06,486 --> 00:09:12,093
Once my credentials are verified, the door to the execution chamber slides silently apart.

101
00:09:13,728 --> 00:09:16,264
Lucien sits on the cold, hard chair with one leg half-bent, gazing up in my direction with keen interest.

102
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:18,500
Heavy iron shackles bind his ankles, hanging through the gaps in the seat.

103
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:21,937
Perhaps having waited too long and grown a bit bored, most of his body now leans against the seat. The collar of his prison uniform is slightly open, displaying a sense of relaxation that seems somewhat out of place.

104
00:09:21,937 --> 00:09:24,340
Lucien: You’re finally here.

105
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:29,512
Lucien: I was just worried you might have changed your mind and didn't want to meet me.

106
00:09:29,512 --> 00:09:31,548
MC: It's my duty, of course I wouldn't hand it over to someone else.

107
00:09:31,548 --> 00:09:36,420
Lucien: So, MC came to see me only because of work?

108
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:38,523
I ignore the familiarity in his tone and calmly proceed to draw the drug.

109
00:09:38,523 --> 00:09:41,593
The vital-signs monitor clamped around his neck displays his real-time pulse. It’s now unexpectedly a few beats faster than when I first entered.

110
00:09:41,593 --> 00:09:43,128
Could this person even be nervous?

111
00:09:43,128 --> 00:09:45,898
Seeing my silence, those dark eyes shift to the injection in my hand, a flicker of curious interest flashing through them.

112
00:09:45,898 --> 00:09:54,307
Lucien: So the memory-erasing execution is carried out through injection? How does it avoid neural damage, then?

113
00:09:54,307 --> 00:09:56,443
MC: The injection contains nanobots that will act according to the program... Never mind.

114
00:09:56,443 --> 00:09:58,378
MC: No matter how much I explain, you’ll forget it all soon anyway.

115
00:09:58,378 --> 00:09:59,914
MC: Stay still. Disinfecting now.

116
00:09:59,914 --> 00:10:02,083
The person before me sighs, a hint of innocence surfacing in the depths of his eyes.

117
00:10:02,083 --> 00:10:09,257
Lucien: This might be my last moment. Can’t MC at least take a bit of our past into account?

118
00:10:10,726 --> 00:10:15,732
His lips are paler than the prison garb. I press my lips together and then still reach for the alcohol-soaked cotton ball with tweezers.

119
00:10:15,732 --> 00:10:21,872
MC: It’s only a memory purge. Why do you say it like it’s a death sentence?

120
00:10:21,872 --> 00:10:27,812
Lucien: But a person's present is shaped by their past.

121
00:10:27,812 --> 00:10:35,687
Lucien: To a certain extent, this is a psychological annihilation of one’s identity.

122
00:10:35,687 --> 00:10:41,995
The alcohol spreads in a faint sheen across his neck. The pungent scent hits my nose, and I instinctively start to speak a little faster.

123
00:10:41,995 --> 00:10:47,401
MC: The system has extracted the memory fragments most critical to you based on your past emotional fluctuations.

124
00:10:47,401 --> 00:10:54,943
MC: After the execution, the prison will broadcast the approved segments daily. As for those that don't meet the standards, they'll be shown after modification.

125
00:10:54,943 --> 00:11:00,149
MC: All in all, it won't affect your cognition... it's not as horrifying as you imagine.

126
00:11:00,149 --> 00:11:06,456
I slowly press the needle tip against his neck. Lucien looks at me calmly; even the heart rate projected in the monitor hardly shows any changes.

127
00:11:06,456 --> 00:11:12,262
I exhale softly, the hand pushing the syringe plunger trembling almost imperceptibly.

128
00:11:12,262 --> 00:11:18,303
The next moment, Lucien’s hand suddenly covers the back of mine, his fingertips slipping unhurriedly between my fingers.

129
00:11:18,303 --> 00:11:20,238
MC: ….!

130
00:11:20,238 --> 00:11:25,577
The clear liquid is pushed into his neck bit by bit. Holding my breath, I can almost feel the warmth of his exhale brushing against my ear.

131
00:11:25,577 --> 00:11:28,748
Lucien: I’ve taught you.

132
00:11:28,748 --> 00:11:37,157
Lucien: Hesitation is the emotion most likely to lead to failure.

133
00:11:37,157 --> 00:11:40,795
Along with his words, the final drop of the drug disappears from the syringe.

134
00:11:40,795 --> 00:11:46,835
The drug takes effect faster than expected. Almost immediately, a faint weariness clouds those eyes that reflect my face like still water.

135
00:11:46,835 --> 00:11:51,540
As if unable to bear the weight of his own head, Lucien’s neck tilts back against the chair, baring a fragile curve to the air.

136
00:11:51,540 --> 00:11:57,147
I count down silently in my heart. Before I even reach five, his eyes slowly drift shut, and the hand entwined with mine falls away.

137
00:11:57,147 --> 00:12:03,320
Amid the ticking of the instruments, I can faintly hear his breathing grow deeper. I slip free from Lucien’s palm, hovering momentarily before letting my hand gently stroke his hair.

138
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:11,463
Cold, soft... If the moonlight could be touched, it would probably feel like this.

139
00:12:11,463 --> 00:12:17,937
I stoop a little, speaking in a quiet murmur.

140
00:12:17,937 --> 00:12:22,108
MC: Thank you for your trouble, Mentor.

141
00:12:22,108 --> 00:12:27,481
MC: But even if the experiment fails, I have a backup plan.

142
00:12:27,481 --> 00:12:37,659
MC: This is the most precious lesson you’ve taught me.

143
00:12:37,926 --> 00:12:40,930
While in prison, MC uses the regular “you” 你 (nǐ), but in the flashback, MC uses 您 (nín), the formal and respectful version of 你, to address Lucien. This is important as it carries nuance that becomes significant later~

144
00:12:42,698 --> 00:12:54,412
??: “...In the year 2230 of the New Era, you enrolled in the School of Psychology and Cognitive Sciences, following the recommendation of the scoring system, with a minor in Sociology…”

145
00:12:54,412 --> 00:12:59,684
??: “...During your first semester, you submitted a paper titled ‘The Role and Development of Psychometrics in Sociology’. The full text reads as follows...”

146
00:12:59,684 --> 00:13:04,723
??: "...In your third year, under your advisor’s guidance, you participated in a symposium on How to Scientifically Quantify Standards for Emotional Auditing, and during the conference..."

147
00:13:04,723 --> 00:13:10,563
A soft mechanical hum echoes through the room. Pale gray wall clearly displays scene after scene like frames from a long, lingering film.

148
00:13:10,563 --> 00:13:17,438
A dark-haired young man appears on the projection. His eyes and brows still hint at youthful inexperience as he walks through the teaching building, yet his calm composure is already evident.

149
00:13:17,438 --> 00:13:21,676
As I watch briefly, I prop my chin on my hand, then let my gaze fall back to Lucien.

150
00:13:21,676 --> 00:13:26,448
It’s been a week since the memory erasure.

151
00:13:26,448 --> 00:13:31,821
Every day, when it’s time for his projected education, he sits quietly on the edge of his bed like this, watching the fragments of his memories.

152
00:13:31,821 --> 00:13:38,161
His expression resembles a sheet of untainted white paper—pure and earnest.

153
00:13:38,161 --> 00:13:44,435
The data indicates that he has not shown any doubt or aversion toward the altered segments of the footage. Judging from this, the execution appears to be effective.

154
00:13:44,435 --> 00:13:50,141
Lost in thought, I’m jotting down the situation on the electronic screen when I suddenly hear him utter a puzzled “Hm?”. I glance up and am momentarily caught off guard.

155
00:13:50,141 --> 00:13:55,748
The memory fragment now playing is a scene from his workday, with the familiar consultation room bathed in warm-toned sunlight.

156
00:13:55,748 --> 00:14:01,955
Lucien rests his chin on one hand, his expression focused as he looks at the wary-faced girl across from him.

157
00:14:01,955 --> 00:14:07,228
…That’s the scene from the first time I sought him for counseling.

158
00:14:07,228 --> 00:14:12,133
Could that afternoon actually be a profound memory for him, too? ...Was my case especially tricky?

159
00:14:12,133 --> 00:14:17,239
A rustle of bedsheets brushes past my ear. Amid the shifting light and shadows, the person beside me turns his head to look at me.

160
00:14:17,239 --> 00:14:26,683
Lucien: ...Miss Section Chief, what was our previous relationship?

161
00:14:26,683 --> 00:14:32,623
It’s the first time he’s spoken since the memory erasure. I steady my inexplicably quickened heartbeat and look into those eyes.

162
00:14:32,623 --> 00:14:37,662
MC: You used to be the psychology instructor at my college.

163
00:14:37,662 --> 00:14:42,434
MC: There was a time when I struggled mentally, and I sought your guidance more than a few times.

164
00:14:42,434 --> 00:14:48,241
Lucien: Even someone as rational as Miss Section Chief experienced a phase like that?

165
00:14:48,241 --> 00:14:51,878
MC: Of course. A person’s stability naturally fluctuates.

166
00:14:51,878 --> 00:14:55,649
MC: Back at the college, you also seemed rather…*

167
00:14:55,649 --> 00:15:02,190
My voice trails off, and out of the corner of my eye, I see Lucien curiously moving closer to me.

168
00:15:02,190 --> 00:15:08,397
Lucien: Also seemed rather what? Can you continue?

169
00:15:08,397 --> 00:15:17,507
Lucien: In addition to the system's objective records, I also want to know what kind of person I am in your eyes.

170
00:15:17,507 --> 00:15:22,146
I observe him with keen intrigue and deliberately furrow my brows.

171
00:15:22,146 --> 00:15:26,384
MC: But this isn’t within the scope of my work.

172
00:15:26,384 --> 00:15:33,659
He blinks, seemingly not expecting me to respond this way. Yet in the next instant, something seems to occur to him, and the corners of his eyes curve slightly.

173
00:15:33,659 --> 00:15:44,104
Lucien: Since Miss Section Chief appears in my memory fragments, you must’ve been my favorite student.

174
00:15:44,104 --> 00:15:51,145
Lucien: For the sake of our past bond... is there really no room for a small favor?

175
00:15:51,145 --> 00:15:56,251
His tone softens a little, and there’s a trace of a familiar smile in his voice.

176
00:15:56,251 --> 00:16:04,394
The memories of the past suddenly flood my heart. Though this maneuvering** feels more clumsy compared to before, it has now become a bit more intriguing.

177
00:16:04,394 --> 00:16:10,267
I can’t help but curl the corners of my lips upward, and under his expectant gaze, I steal a glance at the time.

178
00:16:10,267 --> 00:16:14,138
MC: It’s getting a bit late now.

179
00:16:14,138 --> 00:16:20,379
MC: But I promise you. We’ll continue tomorrow.

180
00:16:20,679 --> 00:16:28,822
Since that day, I began 'working overtime' to 'accompany' Lucien outside of regular work hours.

181
00:16:28,822 --> 00:16:38,299
At first, it was just an occasional arrangement. But after one incident in which I had to respond to his sudden dizziness, it gradually became a fixed part of my schedule.

182
00:16:38,299 --> 00:16:47,109
The system judges that he is having an adverse reaction to the drug, leading to several physical indicators dropping below normal. As a result, his recovery period is extended, and nutritional injections are arranged.

183
00:16:47,109 --> 00:16:54,684
So, in the time I spend with him each day, a caregiving routine is added. But most of the time, it’s him observing my procedures while asking his questions.

184
00:16:54,684 --> 00:17:02,059
…I have to admit, this man’s curiosity is overwhelmingly voracious.

185
00:17:02,059 --> 00:17:07,065
Lucien: How do I know my score from each system update?

186
00:17:07,065 --> 00:17:15,341
MC: The monitoring hall’s equipment displays them publicly. You can also ask the management staff; we can see every prisoner’s score through the system.

187
00:17:15,341 --> 00:17:22,215
Lucien: My heart seems to beat faster every time I receive care.

188
00:17:22,215 --> 00:17:28,923
MC: That’s the nutritional injection taking effect… Strange, your memory of medical knowledge shouldn’t have been affected, right?

189
00:17:28,923 --> 00:17:33,395
Lucien: How much longer is my recovery period?

190
00:17:33,395 --> 00:17:37,066
MC: I’m not sure, let’s wait until your physical indicators return to normal.

191
00:17:37,066 --> 00:17:48,645
Lucien: If I never recover… will MC keep visiting me every day like this?

192
00:17:48,645 --> 00:17:55,053
Adjusting the syringe, my hands still mid-motion, I shoot a glance at him.

193
00:17:55,053 --> 00:17:59,758
MC: Theoretically, yes.

194
00:17:59,758 --> 00:18:04,597
MC: But I can see from the data that you’re recovering quite smoothly.

195
00:18:04,597 --> 00:18:10,604
As if he fails to receive the cherished gift he has set his heart on, his eyes brim with plainly visible disappointment.

196
00:18:10,604 --> 00:18:16,210
I find this version of him somewhat amusing, but as I turn, I hear his contemplative voice behind me.

197
00:18:16,210 --> 00:18:23,218
Lucien: But do you really think the system can’t be deceived by data, MC?

198
00:18:23,218 --> 00:18:33,830
Lucien: It evaluates efficiently yet never delves into the causes. If someone wanted to exploit it… it wouldn’t be difficult, would it?

199
00:18:33,830 --> 00:18:36,967
MC: …!

200
00:18:36,967 --> 00:18:42,907
His voice carries a note of skepticism as if he’s simply asking an innocent question. But I keenly pick up on the faint arrogance in his tone.

201
00:18:42,907 --> 00:18:48,447
I set down the syringe and slowly turn around.

202
00:18:48,447 --> 00:18:53,452
MC: ...Why do you think that?

203
00:18:53,452 --> 00:19:00,494
Lucien: Because… it seems I’ve already succeeded in tricking it.

204
00:19:00,494 --> 00:19:07,935
Lucien: My adverse reaction to the drug, that’s the system’s misjudgment.

205
00:19:07,935 --> 00:19:13,575
As I stare at him in bewilderment and surprise, he narrows his eyes, a sly glint flashing in them.

206
00:19:13,575 --> 00:19:24,788
Lucien: I haven’t actually felt any discomfort since the execution, just some habitual insomnia. So during the day, I occasionally feel fatigued.

207
00:19:24,788 --> 00:19:31,762
Lucien: The other day, an interesting thought suddenly came to me while recalling my past medical knowledge.

208
00:19:31,762 --> 00:19:39,905
Lucien: Symptoms like 'fatigue' and 'mental lethargy' are actually among the adverse effects of the drug.

209
00:19:39,905 --> 00:19:49,583
Lucien: If I deliberately exhibit more signs of a drug reaction, how would the system judge that? …That idea suddenly popped into my head.

210
00:19:49,583 --> 00:19:55,523
He raises a finger, tapping lightly at his temple.

211
00:19:55,523 --> 00:20:10,106
Lucien: So I tried feeding a few controlled and precise cues to the Iris device, like intermittent accelerated breathing, and...

212
00:20:10,106 --> 00:20:15,712
MC: ...Sudden dizziness.

213
00:20:15,712 --> 00:20:22,286
The image of him from some time ago—eyes half-lidded as he leans against the headboard—crosses my mind. My palm tightens slightly.

214
00:20:22,286 --> 00:20:27,459
Lucien meets my gaze without affirmation or denial, a clear smile showing in his eyes.

215
00:20:27,459 --> 00:20:37,570
Lucien: You see, every piece of data it holds is actually precise.

216
00:20:37,570 --> 00:20:45,279
Lucien: Yet even so, it still arrives at an erroneous judgment.

217
00:20:45,279 --> 00:20:51,820
His dark eyes twinkle, like a child who has found the answer through his own hard work, laced with pure joy and a faint sense of pride.

218
00:20:51,820 --> 00:20:56,692
I stare intently at the curve of Lucien’s lips, a slight chill creeping vaguely up my spine.

219
00:20:56,692 --> 00:21:02,832
Even though his memories were clearly erased, and everything he receives is filtered by the system, how come a thought like that still born?

220
00:21:02,832 --> 00:21:07,838
Is he playing a prank? Or… were his previous memories not completely wiped?

221
00:21:07,838 --> 00:21:14,346
I try to find an inkling of jest in his refined brows and eyes, but my heartbeat accelerates uncontrollably.

222
00:21:14,346 --> 00:21:20,553
There seems to be some kind of unexplained presence, and an unexpected development has emerged.

223
00:21:20,553 --> 00:21:24,657
Two notification boxes suddenly pop up in my lens display, severing the tangled web of my thoughts.

224
00:21:24,657 --> 00:21:30,030
System: Ten minutes remain until this month's system score update. Please proceed to the monitoring hall.

225
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:37,305
System: If no relevant action is taken, the system will automatically assume control and reclaim the data.

226
00:21:37,305 --> 00:21:43,512
My gaze flickers slightly as I slowly begin to speak.

227
00:21:43,512 --> 00:21:47,316
MC: …Alright, story time is over.

228
00:21:47,316 --> 00:21:51,588
MC: You should prepare yourself to undergo a new round of scoring by the system.

229
00:21:51,588 --> 00:21:57,795
Lucien: You think what I just said was nothing but fantasy?

230
00:21:57,795 --> 00:22:02,534
MC: That would be the best-case scenario. Otherwise, you should start worrying about your own safety.

231
00:22:02,534 --> 00:22:08,407
The air suddenly falls silent. Our eyes lock, as if we are using our gazes as blades, confronting each other invisibly.

232
00:22:08,407 --> 00:22:13,346
MC: If you’ve been harboring this kind of dangerous mindset all along, it will definitely affect the evaluation.

233
00:22:13,346 --> 00:22:19,052
MC: Should your score continue to fall short, your memory will be erased again.

234
00:22:19,052 --> 00:22:25,526
MC: Of course, you can demonstrate it right in front of me. Show me how you’d outsmart the system’s evaluation… if you’re really as clever as you say.

235
00:22:25,526 --> 00:22:29,397
Like a butterfly’s wings flutter, he blinks slowly and softly.

236
00:22:29,397 --> 00:22:32,134
Lucien: Sure.

237
00:22:32,134 --> 00:22:37,907
Lucien: But if I act as I please, wouldn't that get you in trouble?

238
00:22:37,907 --> 00:22:41,711
He speaks in quite a good mood, tilting his chin toward the camera in the corner.

239
00:22:41,711 --> 00:22:48,319
MC: Don’t worry. As the medical section chief, I have the authority to remove certain information that’s unfavorable to me.

240
00:22:48,319 --> 00:22:52,724
MC: But if you’re deliberately wasting my time…

241
00:22:52,724 --> 00:22:58,631
I ease down onto the edge of the bed. Leaning in close to Lucien’s ear, I lower my voice to a whisper.

242
00:22:58,631 --> 00:23:06,273
MC: The next time I punish you, I won't be so gentle.

243
00:23:07,140 --> 00:23:10,644
*: I translated the word as ‘seemed’ for brevity and naturalness, but 表现 (biǎo xiàn— literally “manifested conduct”) conveys more nuance. It refers to the way one’s actions are outwardly displayed or expressed, how his observable actions are like. (1/2)

244
00:23:10,644 --> 00:23:13,481
Combined with what he said afterward, his curiosity here isn’t merely about what he seemed like, but how she perceived him. (2/2)

245
00:23:13,481 --> 00:23:16,918
**: In this context, "maneuvering" refers to the act of carefully guiding or manipulating someone or something in order to achieve a goal rather than the usual ‘move carefully’. (1/2)

246
00:23:16,918 --> 00:23:20,889
"斡旋" (wò xuán) is often translated as "to mediate" or "to negotiate," but here it carries the nuance of subtle psychological or emotional maneuvering that she employs to achieve her objective~ (2/2)

247
00:23:21,523 --> 00:23:31,101
I draw myself upright and lean back with unflappable composure, observing him from the side.

248
00:23:31,101 --> 00:23:36,040
Lucien, however, doesn’t show a hint of surprise or hesitation. Instead, he calmly rolls up his cuffs, revealing a section of his slender, cold-white forearm.

249
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:40,378
He then takes a syringe from the nearby equipment cart, adjusts it somewhat unskilfully, and injects half the dose of nutritional solution into himself.

250
00:23:40,378 --> 00:23:44,416
A faint sheen of sweat seeps from his neck—a common reaction to high-concentration nutritional fluid entering the body.

251
00:23:44,416 --> 00:23:47,453
I frown, despite myself, I can’t resist speaking:

252
00:23:47,453 --> 00:23:51,023
MC: The nutritional injection will affect the cardiac rhythm, so it needs to be administered slowly.

253
00:23:51,023 --> 00:23:57,931
Lucien: I know. But there’s no time to let it take effect gradually now.

254
00:23:57,931 --> 00:24:06,574
Lucien: Before the system updates the score, I need to calibrate my heart rate to the "standard" rate to pass the examination.

255
00:24:06,574 --> 00:24:10,278
The countdown’s red glare reflects in his eyes, adding a touch of unpredictability.

256
00:24:10,278 --> 00:24:17,353
Lucien: No need to worry... I also cherish this body you’ve so earnestly tended to, MC.

257
00:24:17,353 --> 00:24:26,664
Lucien: 1.5 milliliters is exactly the precise dose to achieve the ideal condition without causing excessive burden on my body.

258
00:24:26,664 --> 00:24:30,969
His tone is breezy and unquestionably assured, as if everything is under his control, compelling others to intuitively want to believe him.

259
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:34,740
This familiar feeling gradually overlaps with my memory, slightly startling me.

260
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:38,110
The seconds on the digital clock silently tick in the corner of our vision, then snap abruptly to the full hour.

261
00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:42,615
Almost the next second, a prompt box indicating a successful score update pops up in my lens' view.

262
00:24:42,615 --> 00:24:47,754
I stifle my rapidly beating heart and move my fingertips. Suddenly, the screen flickers, and a photo of Lucien appears with a flashing bright number — '42'.

263
00:24:47,754 --> 00:24:51,192
…This is indeed a score within the safe range.

264
00:24:51,192 --> 00:24:55,196
My eyes widen, my mind even goes blank for a fleeting moment.

265
00:24:55,196 --> 00:24:59,768
I can't believe it. He really fooled the system's review... How did he do it? Did he simply rely on the injection to change a few physical indicators?

266
00:24:59,768 --> 00:25:03,906
How is that possible... If it were that simple, wouldn't all criminals who receive the nutritional injections be able to get out of prison?

267
00:25:03,906 --> 00:25:13,083
Lucien: Because when the system evaluates a human's physical or even psychological condition, it simultaneously examines multiple indicators.

268
00:25:13,083 --> 00:25:19,590
Lucien's voice rises beside me as if he had heard the question in my heart, as though he’s leisurely explaining a problem set.

269
00:25:19,590 --> 00:25:28,768
Lucien: For example, to determine whether someone agrees with the system, it will retrieve their heart rate, blood pressure, and respiratory rate when exposed to related information.

270
00:25:28,768 --> 00:25:34,341
Lucien: Of course, a single fluctuation can't fool it.

271
00:25:34,341 --> 00:25:46,354
Lucien: Fortunately, I’ve been receiving nutritional injection care during this period. While watching videos, my heart rate and blood pressure were both elevated, naturally helping to avoid the system judging any feelings of disgust.

272
00:25:46,354 --> 00:25:52,494
Lucien: Then, coupled with some seemingly genuine microexpressions...

273
00:25:52,494 --> 00:25:57,800
He casually flicks the syringe's needle and gives me a calm, slightly confused smile.

274
00:25:57,800 --> 00:26:00,437
...This expression is not unfamiliar.

275
00:26:00,437 --> 00:26:03,307
Every day, when watching his memory footage, Lucien always shows this gentle, harmless expression.

276
00:26:03,307 --> 00:26:07,378
MC: You're the first person I've seen who could ‘relapse into old patterns’ even after memory erasure and system re-education.

277
00:26:07,378 --> 00:26:12,250
MC: You really were born for prison.

278
00:26:12,250 --> 00:26:17,323
I control my slightly trembling breath, my gaze lingering on his face for a long time, my tone tinged with mockery.

279
00:26:17,323 --> 00:26:21,928
Lucien, however, gently shakes his head, as if somewhat disagreeing.

280
00:26:21,928 --> 00:26:29,103
Lucien: I originally thought the same. But just now, a new conjecture suddenly occurred to me.

281
00:26:29,103 --> 00:26:35,910
Lucien: Since I can trick the system now, perhaps I could’ve done the same thing back then.

282
00:26:35,910 --> 00:26:38,780
MC: ...What are you implying?

283
00:26:38,780 --> 00:26:45,087
Lucien: I mean, what if being imprisoned was the result of my own choice?

284
00:26:45,087 --> 00:26:48,792
He casts down his gaze and begins to speak unhurriedly.

285
00:26:48,792 --> 00:26:57,034
Lucien: Suppose this counterintuitive conclusion holds, then there must be something here that I want to gain or achieve.

286
00:26:57,034 --> 00:27:03,108
Lucien: But what is it that makes this prison special compared to the outside world?

287
00:27:03,108 --> 00:27:07,313
His voice pauses, as if he's deducing something, yet also as if he's talking to himself.

288
00:27:07,313 --> 00:27:14,254
Lucien: This place is on an island, its environment is closed off and highly dependent on the system.

289
00:27:14,254 --> 00:27:22,563
Lucien: Dietary plans, medication dosages... the system makes real-time adjustments based on each prisoner's condition.

290
00:27:22,563 --> 00:27:28,937
Lucien: So there's no need to wait for the bi-monthly scoring to know how it responds

291
00:27:28,937 --> 00:27:37,080
Lucien: Looking at it this way, it's the most perfect place to test the system's vulnerabilities.

292
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:40,350
MC: …..

293
00:27:40,350 --> 00:27:45,456
His eyes glimmer faintly. I meet his gaze for a beat, and a 'pfft' slips out before I can stop it.

294
00:27:45,456 --> 00:27:49,694
MC: Sounds interesting, but this experiment you describe seems to have only the setting and a test subject.

295
00:27:49,694 --> 00:27:54,366
MC: For a complete experiment, isn't something missing? Like someone who runs through the entire process, an observer?

296
00:27:54,366 --> 00:28:00,573
The chains clink softly as Lucien leans slightly toward me, my doubtful expression reflected in his eyes.

297
00:28:00,573 --> 00:28:05,512
His low voice seems probing, yet there's also some sort of genuine admiration in it.

298
00:28:05,512 --> 00:28:11,252
Lucien: That's something I'll need you to confirm.

299
00:28:11,252 --> 00:28:20,529
Lucien: Estimating from the time data in my memory projection, you entered the prison system exactly six months before I was sentenced.

300
00:28:20,529 --> 00:28:29,639
Lucien: Regarding timing or identity, you seem like someone tailor-made for this experiment.

301
00:28:29,639 --> 00:28:33,444
MC: …That’s enough.

302
00:28:33,444 --> 00:28:36,581
MC: You're even using coincidences to piece together your fantasies now?

303
00:28:36,581 --> 00:28:39,617
Lucien: Of course there are coincidences in this world.

304
00:28:39,617 --> 00:28:45,524
Lucien: But when they happen one after another, that results from a guiding push.

305
00:28:45,524 --> 00:28:52,032
His fingertips brush across my face, carrying a warmth so faint it’s almost not there, like the rising steam from a teacup that afternoon. His softened voice seems to hold a subtle grievance.

306
00:28:52,032 --> 00:28:57,871
Lucien: I understand that people need to leave themselves some room to maneuver.

307
00:28:57,871 --> 00:29:05,814
Lucien: But I’ve already proven the system’s flaws; this experiment can end here.

308
00:29:05,814 --> 00:29:10,019
Lucien: MC, can’t you be honest with me now?

309
00:29:10,019 --> 00:29:14,691
Though he’s asking a question, there’s unmistakable certainty in his expression. It’s as if he already knows the answer before I open my mouth.

310
00:29:14,691 --> 00:29:18,862
Just like that sun-drenched afternoon, it makes me momentarily dazed.

311
00:29:20,063 --> 00:29:22,967
.....

312
00:29:22,967 --> 00:29:27,672
Lucien: Then do you genuinely hold unwavering faith in the system’s judgment?

313
00:29:27,672 --> 00:29:33,645
I met the gaze of the man on the sofa. For a brief moment, we looked into each other’s eyes and saw a similar, unspoken danger that we both understood.

314
00:29:33,645 --> 00:29:37,783
Neither of us knew who curved their lips first, but we both chuckled at the same time.

315
00:29:37,783 --> 00:29:42,289
I propped my chin up with one hand and spoke with great interest.

316
00:29:42,289 --> 00:29:44,758
MC: My mentor and I are truly in sync.

317
00:29:44,758 --> 00:29:50,031
MC: Earlier, we were talking about employment… So what advice are you going to give me?*

318
00:29:50,031 --> 00:29:53,435
Lucien: Clever girl.

319
00:29:53,435 --> 00:29:58,173
He crinkled his eyes into crescents and tapped on “prison doctor” in my employment recommendation.

320
00:29:58,173 --> 00:30:05,815
Lucien: Though the prison is a closed environment, it’s an ideal place to conduct experiments and verify certain hypotheses of ours.

321
00:30:05,815 --> 00:30:11,789
Lucien: Perhaps, would MC be willing to enter the prison system early?

322
00:30:11,789 --> 00:30:14,592
MC: Are you trying to gain certain conveniences through me?

323
00:30:14,592 --> 00:30:21,033
Lucien: No, you only need to be a witness.

324
00:30:21,033 --> 00:30:24,303
My gaze fell on his refined, handsome face as I pondered with interest.

325
00:30:24,303 --> 00:30:28,508
It really does sound intriguing. Where I work doesn’t make much difference to me anyway.

326
00:30:28,508 --> 00:30:33,146
Since that’s the case, why not work with someone of my own ‘kind’ to uncover the system’s flaws?

327
00:30:33,146 --> 00:30:37,051
If it fails... there's no real danger.

328
00:30:37,051 --> 00:30:40,521
I can keep this secret to myself, tuck my tail away, and climb upward obediently within the existing system.

329
00:30:40,521 --> 00:30:47,529
And while I’m at it, I can take good care of my poor mentor— after all, he’s about to spend the rest of his life helplessly in a territory under my control.

330
00:30:47,529 --> 00:30:51,133
But if his conclusion turns out to be correct—

331
00:30:53,069 --> 00:30:55,271
I curve the corners of my lips into a smile and lean forward to take the unspent syringe from his hand.

332
00:30:55,271 --> 00:30:58,141
MC: I was worried that after the memory erasure, you'd forget your original purpose and spend the rest of your life here, completely unaware.

333
00:30:58,141 --> 00:31:00,310
MC: Fortunately, the outcome of this experiment turned out just as you predicted, Mentor Xu.

334
00:31:00,310 --> 00:31:02,546
A faint tremor travels up from beneath my fingertips as Lucien seems to let out a few low chuckles.

335
00:31:02,546 --> 00:31:05,116
His pounding heartbeat, carried on the scorching heat of his body, lays this intricate deception bare before me.

336
00:31:05,116 --> 00:31:08,186
Lucien: So that’s what MC is thinking.

337
00:31:08,186 --> 00:31:14,860
Lucien: I thought that if I failed, you'd be more than happy to keep me imprisoned under your watch forever.

338
00:31:14,860 --> 00:31:16,729
MC: Am I really that cunning in my mentor's eyes?

339
00:31:16,729 --> 00:31:22,502
Lucien: After all, a clever girl would never leave herself with only one option.

340
00:31:22,502 --> 00:31:25,706
I let out a light laugh, steadying my heartbeat, which had long been racing with excitement, and projected the internal data from my lens into the air.

341
00:31:25,706 --> 00:31:28,509
A vast array of criminal data and files shimmers before our eyes—a treasure trove that would dazzle any researcher.

342
00:31:28,509 --> 00:31:30,678
Resting my chin on Lucien’s shoulder, I raise my voice with a dash of boast.

343
00:31:30,678 --> 00:31:33,381
MC: I've already screened the profiles of these criminals. Hmm... twenty-eight of them have backgrounds related to medicine.

344
00:31:33,381 --> 00:31:36,151
MC: What if we select half of them and give them subtle pointers about your experimental approach to trick the system?

345
00:31:36,151 --> 00:31:38,053
MC: Given their foundational knowledge, they’re likely to catch on fast.

346
00:31:38,053 --> 00:31:40,122
I speak with ardor and hear him chuckle.

347
00:31:40,122 --> 00:31:50,534
Lucien: I think, it would be better to choose people who don’t have a medical background but do have a rebellious mindset toward the system as the control group.

348
00:31:50,534 --> 00:31:57,676
Lucien: All in all, aside from skill, the courage to question is even more important.

349
00:31:59,110 --> 00:32:02,047
MC: Okay, I like this design~

350
00:32:02,047 --> 00:32:06,085
MC: Then we can also flag those whose stance toward the system is unclear and gradually shift their position.

351
00:32:06,085 --> 00:32:10,290
MC: Only with enough subjects can our experiment keep going for a long time...

352
00:32:10,290 --> 00:32:16,630
Lucien strokes my head approvingly, and I pull on the collar around his neck with a smile.

353
00:32:16,630 --> 00:32:20,268
The hazy darkness muffles the whispers in the shadows and conceals the hidden ambitions and secrets.

354
00:32:20,268 --> 00:32:26,675
From now on, this prison is a paradise that belongs to us.

355
00:32:26,675 --> 00:32:36,820
Lucien: Then, let the experiment begin.

356
00:32:36,820 --> 00:32:44,061
If you're wondering whether the collar MC pulls on refers to clothing, it's not. The term "颈环" (jǐng huán) specifically refers to a ring-like device worn around the neck. Sth sth XM giving her approval as mentor but mc pulling on his collar as an act of control can be read as symbolising how their power imbalance (Mentor-Student, Prisoner-Executioner) somewhat balances itself ig LOL.

357
00:32:44,061 --> 00:32:52,638
*: Remember what I mentioned in the previous note about MC using the formal "you" (您) earlier in the flashback? In part 4 of flashback, she shifts to the informal "你" (nǐ), and that shift is intentional as it marks a turning point in their interaction (1/2)

358
00:32:52,638 --> 00:33:07,521
By switching to "你," MC is effectively dropping the formality. She’s no longer addressing Lucien with the distance and deference of a mentor-student relationship. Instead, she speaks to him as an equal, or at least as someone she’s willing to engage with more boldly, directly, and on more intimate terms. (2/2)

359
00:33:07,521 --> 00:33:20,303
I think... that’s all feel free to drop by my comment if you want to read my afterwords (though it’s mostly rambles *kicked*)